法規內容.條文內容:
“Proof of ROC nationality” referred to in Article 5, Paragraph 1, Subparagraph 5 of the Act means any of the following documents:
1. Official printout of a ROC household registration record;
2. Personal identification card;
3. Original ROC household registration record;
4. Passport;
5. Proof of nationality;
6. Overseas Chinese Registration Certificate;
7. Overseas Chinese Identity Certificate;
8. Proof of ROC nationality in respect of one of the parents of the applicant, together with birth certificate of the applicant;
9. Other proof of nationality approved by the Ministry of Interior.
The Overseas Chinese Identity Certificate mentioned in Subparagraph 7 of the previous paragraph does not include those issued to applicants who have obtained such a Certificate by providing Document of proof of Chinese ethnicity in their applications.

The following information shall be stated on an Overseas Chinese Identity Certificate:
1. Certificate number;
2. Chinese name;
3. Foreign name and alias;
4. Date of birth;
5. Issuing authority;
6. Issue date;
7. Validity period;
8. Statement of whether Certificate application had been made on the basis of document of proof of Chinese ethnicity;
9. Other matters designated by the competent authority.
An Overseas Chinese Identity Certificate issued for military service purposes shall also specify the personal identification card number of the applicant.

The competent authority, in processing applications for Overseas Chinese Identity Certificate or Overseas Chinese Identity Endorsement, may obtain online information from the relevant customs authority about entries into and departures from the ROC by travelers, and may also obtain the following information via the connection of information systems:
1. Revision of nationality information from Nationality Administration System of the Ministry of Interior;
2. Household registration information from the Household Registration & Military Services Administration System of the Ministry of Interior.
